---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import MirrorBrowser from "../components/MirrorBrowser.astro";
---

<Base title="Firmware — N9 Archive" active="firmware">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-screen-xl px-6 pt-16 pb-10 md:px-10 md:pt-20 lg:px-16">
    <p class="mb-4 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-n9-500">
      Firmware images
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-serif text-4xl font-normal leading-[1.05] tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl"
      style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48;"
    >
      The files that bring it back.
    </h1>
    <div
      class="mt-8 max-w-[40rem] space-y-5 font-serif text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.7] text-n9-200 md:text-[1.125rem]"
      style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 16;"
    >
      <p>
        These are the original Nokia firmware images for the RM-696 — the
        files a flasher writes onto the device when something has gone wrong
        or when you're starting fresh. <code class="rounded bg-n9-800/70 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[0.92em] text-n9-100">PR_LEGACY</code>
        is the main firmware payload; the <code class="rounded bg-n9-800/70 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[0.92em] text-n9-100">EMMC</code>
        image is the user-data partition, region-specific.
      </p>
      <p>
        The <a href="/guides/flashing" class="archive-link">flashing guide</a>
        walks through the actual procedure end-to-end, and the
        <a href="/guides/flasher-troubleshooting" class="archive-link">troubleshooting
        notes</a> cover the parts that tend to go wrong.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-screen-xl px-6 pb-20 md:px-10 lg:px-16">
    <MirrorBrowser rootPrefix="images/" />
  </section>
</Base>
